---
const metrics = [
  { v: 'Bound', l: 'format inspectors expect' },
  { v: '120', l: 'pre-formatted pages' },
  { v: '2', l: 'formats for counter & file' },
];
---

<section class="bg-neutral-50">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-14 2xl:max-w-full">
    <div class="mb-8 max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-blue">A Dealer Scenario</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-800 md:text-3xl">What "Ready" Looks Like</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-6 rounded-3xl bg-blue p-8 text-white shadow-2xl shadow-blue/20 md:grid-cols-5 lg:p-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <p class="font-serif text-xl leading-relaxed lg:text-2xl">
          "The inspector asked for the acquisition and disposition record. I pulled the <span class="font-bold text-yellow">bound book</span>, flipped to the date, and every line was already in the right column. No scrambling, no spreadsheets — just the log, the way it's expected to read."
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-blue-100">— Illustrative scenario based on common FFL record-keeping requirements</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-blue-200">This is an illustrative example, not a verified customer review.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:col-span-2">
        {metrics.map((m) => (
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/20 bg-white/10 p-4 transition hover:bg-white/15">
            <div class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-yellow">{m.v}</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-blue-100">{m.l}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
